metadata.name: Tierra
metadata.description:
Tierra
Art number 1

His traces of the sea stepped on the earth and formed his gaze.  And in her hands she hugged them as if they were one.  She did not ask their names nor did she want to know where they were from or where they came from because wherever they went she would always keep them company.

Sus huellas de mar pisaron la tierra y formaron su mirada.  Y entre sus manos los abrazó como si fueran uno solo.  No preguntó sus nombres ni quiso saber de dónde eran, ni de dónde venían, porque dondequiera que fueran siempre les haría compañía
